Step 1 Create a project with spring initializer with all the dependencies
Step 2 Configure the database in application properties

    spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/mydb1
    spring.datasource.username=root
    spring.datasource.password=Potter5595
    spring.datasource.driver-class-name=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver
    spring.jpa.show-sql=true

Step 3 Make sure the db specified in url exists..If not create it
Step 4 run the command ''''mvn clean install''''
Step 5 run the command '''' mvn spring-boot:run ''''
Step 6 To use mysql use the command '''' mysql -u root -p ''''

